    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat with the <strong>sliced onion </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p><p>Tip: Add a splash of oil if your pan is looking a little dry!</p><p>Add the <strong>ground allspice</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>cinnamon </strong>and <strong>remaining cumin </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant, then add the <strong>bulgur wheat </strong>and <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>stock</strong> and cook, covered, for 5-7 min or until the water has absorbed and the bulgur is cooked with a bite</p>",
